#!/usr/bin/env python3
# runnerctl — sudoless, config-driven pool manager for self-hosted GitHub Actions runners.
# Single file, Python 3.6+ standard library only.
# https://github.com/flinner/gh-runnerctl
#
# Architecture: ONE supervisor process (`runnerctl daemon`) owns all runner
# processes as direct children, restarting each independently with backoff.
# The supervisor is hosted either as a single user-level systemd service
# (runnerctl.service) or as a detached process on hosts without a systemd
# user bus. All GitHub work (registration, busy checks, interactive token
# prompts) lives in the CLI commands; the daemon needs no tokens and is
# controlled with SIGHUP (rescan) plus per-runner marker files.

